para_trans: 2. Conditions: -

1) The construction work should be taken up within the time frame of completion with proper planning and follow-up action as per the detailed budget with regard to the ancillary provisions which have been taken into consideration in a rough manner.

2) The budget should be attested by the concerned Superintending Engineer B Chief Engineer of the Public Works Department as well as the competent officer of the Consumer Department before commencing the work.
3) Special care should be taken to ensure that no revised administrative approval is required for this work.
4) Department of Environment, Government Decisions, No. Action should be taken as per the guidelines mentioned in ENV-2013 / Q. No. 177 / T.No. 1, dated 10th January, 2014.
5) The Public Works Department should deal with the issues related to the work presented as per Government Decision No.BDG-2017 / Q.No. 60 / Building-2, dated 07.07.2017.
6) Construction should not be undertaken without budgetary provision for the present work.

3.
